<TEXT>
   Sweden's King Carl XVI Gustaf and Queen Silvia, in
Dallas as part of a nationwide tour to celebrate Sweden's ties to
the United States, took in some Texas-style entertainment _
barbeque, broncos and bullriding.
   The queen arrived at the Mesquite Rodeo on Friday in a crimson
western-style fringe dress, a giant white hat, and gold lizard skin
boots. The king opted for a casual look of a checkered sports
jacket and tassled loafers and hat. He also woore an engraved belt
buckle the size of a fist.
   Before the rodeo, they ate barbecue under a yellow-striped tent.
   ``We had a glimpse of (rodeo) in Calgary the other day. It will
be fun to see the difference between their revue and this one,''
the king said.
   A crowd of about 4,000 people cheered as the flag of Sweden was
introduced and again when the queen and king were presented.
