<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
   
   JESSE JACKSON, asked Friday if he would accept the No. 2 spot on
the Democratic ticket with Dukakis: ``It's a bit premature to be
giving out coronation roses for the governor and taps for me. We're
now moving into the last lap of a significant race, and I'm a
long-distance runner. I look forward to it.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, in Philadelphia at his first one-on-one debate
with Jesse Jackson: ``The two remaining _ and I guess that makes us
the leading _ candidates for the Democratic nomination are the son
of immigrants from Massachusetts and a black man who grew up poor
in South Carolina. I think that says everything there is to say
about this country.''
   
   FRANK FAHRENKOPF, Jr., Republican National Chairman, calling for
party unity at a discordant Nevada GOP convention: ``The old and
new faces in our party must unite and work to defeat our common
enemy.''
