<HEAD>Jackson Official Says Glickman Should Support Jesse _ Or Else</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jesse Jackson's campaign co-chairman in
Sedgwick County says he will campaign against Rep. Dan Glickman if
the Kansas Democrat doesn't support Jackson for the presidential
nomination.
   Glickman, an uncommitted ``super delegate'' to the Democratic
convention, said Friday night that he thinks Charles McAfee was
speaking ``in the heat of a campaign, and, besides, I don't respond
to threats.''
   McAfee said of his comments, ``I didn't make a threat, it's just
the truth. I'm not a politician. I don't play games.''
   He said he served notice to Glickman, a former supporter of Rep.
Richard Gephardt's presidential campaign, two weeks ago at a
gathering of Jackson's Kansas delegates.
   ``My words were, `I love the boy like a son, but if he doesn't
back Jackson, I will campaign against him,''' McAfee said.
   ``Everyone comes to the black community and asks for help,'' he
said. ``Just when does anybody think we can expect something in
return? I keep saying over and over again, how long?''
   The confrontation came on the eve of Democratic conventions
scheduled today in the state's five congressional districts, where
the first 26 Kansas delegates to the Democratic National Convention
were to be chosen.
</TEXT>
