<1ST_LINE>r a PM-VideoStoreMurder     04-23 0310</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Video Store Murder,0316</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Robber Kills Pregnant Woman; Baby Later Delivered By Ceasarean
Section</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEARNS, Utah (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A pregnant woman shopping in a video store
with her three children was shot to death by a robber, authorities
said, but doctors were able to save her nearly full-term fetus by a
Ceasarean section delivery.
   The robber shot Anna Holmes, 31, of West Valley City as he was
leaving the video store Friday night, apparently because he was
unhappy with the amount of cash he had gotten, said Salt Lake
County Sheriff's Lt. Bernard Bailey.
   The gunman entered the Voyager Video store at 8:40 p.m., milled
around for a few minutes, then turned to the clerk and demanded
cash, Bailey said.
   The clerk complied, he said, but the robber grumbled about
wanting more money. He turned to leave, but as he left he pulled
out a small caliber, silver-colored handgun, put it to Holmes' head
and pulled the trigger.
   Witnesses told Bailey the man then said, ``That'll take care of
her.''
   The amount of cash taken was undetermined.
   In addition to the children whose ages ranged from 5 to 13 years
old, and the clerk, about eight other people witnessed the
shooting. All said it was unprovoked, Bailey said.
   Holmes was taken to Pioneer Valley Hospital and later
transported by helicopter to the University of Utah Health Sciences
Center, where she was pronounced dead, said nursing supervisor Lynn
Evans.
   Her daughter was delivered by Caesarean section and was in
critical condition, Evans said. The baby was about 32-34 weeks
along, which is almost full-term, but was suffering from lack of
oxygen.
   Witnesses described the gunman as in his 30s or 40s, about 6
feet tall with graying hair and wearing a plaid shirt and blue
jeans.Police searching for the man were preparing a composite
drawing from witness descriptions, deputies said.
</TEXT>
