<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--BarRaids     04-23 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bar Raids,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Arrest 86 In Nightclub Raids</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police raided seven bars and
nightclubs and rounded up about 80 Filipino barmaids and dancers
and six foreigners in a crackdown on prostitution and illegal
aliens, police said Saturday.
   Police said the four Britons and two Australians were arrested
and detained pending deportation proceedings. They were accused of
either managing or owning bars without valid business visas.
   The Friday night raids in the Ermita tourist district brought to
about 2,000 the number of people, mostly women, rounded up since
Manila police chief Brig. Gen. Alfredo Lim began cracking down last
month on establishments he claims are fronts for prostitution.
   Lim said the women, officially listed as waitresses,
receptionists and dancers, were released after medical checkups. He
said up to 80 percent of them were found to be infected with
sexually transmitted diseases.
