<2ND_LINE>AM-Car Killing,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Runs Over, Kills Wrong Man, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman killed a man by running over his head
with her car, then told police she had mistaken him for her
boyfriend, authorities said.
   Donna Faye Williams, 31, was charged Friday with first-degree
murder in the death of Joel Robinson, 28, who died of massive head
injuries.
   Williams told police that she had mistaken Robinson for her
boyfriend, Louis Teague, 31, when she knocked him down with her
car, then returned to drive over his head.
   ``Whether she knew who he was is unknown,'' said Jeff Jamieson,
assistant circuit attorney. ``She said she thought it was her
boyfriend.''
   The incident occurred shortly after 1:30 a.m. Friday in front of
Robinson's north side home, where Teague and Williams had quarreled
earlier, Jamieson said.
   Williams got into her car and intentionally rammed the car
parked in front of hers. Robinson and Teague came outside to stop
her, Jamieson said.
   When Williams tried to sideswipe the parked car, she hit the car
and Robinson, knocking him to the ground, Jamieson said. Williams
then drove down the street, turned around and came back, running
over Robinson, police said.
   Williams, arrested at the scene about 20 minutes later, gave a
taped admission to police, Jamieson said.
</TEXT>
