<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   To drawn-out chants of ``Bruuuuce Bruuuuce,''
rock music idol Bruce Springsteen opened a five-night concert
series at the Los Angeles Sports Arena, his first in the city in 2{
years.
   Friday night's performance before a crowd of 15,000 was slightly
more intimate than Springsteen's ``Born in the USA Tour''
performances at the nearby Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum in 1985.
More than 80,000 people jammed the Coliseum for each of those shows.
   The 22-city ``Tunnel of Love'' tour, featuring Springsteen,
known as ``the Boss'' to his fans, and his E Street Band continues
in Los Angeles through Thursday.
   ``He makes you into a leader,'' said fan Adam Schellin, 19, of
suburban Simi Valley. ``He pulls me up when I'm down.''
