<HEAD>Mother Accused of Killing Baby Placed Under Suicide Watch</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Woman who admitted drowning her colicky
two-month-old son was under a court-ordered suicide watch in jail
Saturday because of fears that the might take her own life.
   Brooklyn Criminal Court Judge Micki Scherer ordered the suicide
watch during Lucrezia Gentile's arraignment Friday on a charge of
second-degree murder in the death of her son Stephen.
   The order ``means a correction officer checks on her every 15
minutes,'' said Ruby Ryles, spokeswoman for the city Department of
Correction.
   The judge set bail at $75,000 and told Mrs. Gentile she may not
have unsupervised visits with her 7-year-old son, John Jr.
   Mrs. Gentile, 36, was arrested after admitting she lied when she
told police her son was snatched from her on the street by
kidnappers.
   Police said she admitted drowning the baby in the bathtub
Wednesday morning, dressing him, putting him in a plastic garbage
bag and dumped him in a trash can two blocks from her home.
   Police said her husband, John, a 32-year-old U.S. marshal, knew
nothing about circumstances of the child's death.
   Her lawyer, John DePaola, said she suffered from postpartum
depression. He said she had run up about $20,000 in medical bills
after having surgery to correct an infertility problem, then she
had gone through a difficult pregnancy.

