<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A London-bound Continental Airlines jet with more
than 200 people aboard returned to the Newark, N.J., airport after
a cockpit indicator light showed a problem with a hydraulic line, a
Continental spokesman said.
   The light came on shortly after takeoff Thursday night from
Newark International Airport, and the pilot requested permission to
return to Newark as a precaution to have fixed the line, which
serves an engine, spokesman Ned Walker said at company headquarters
in Houston.
