<TEXT>
   A woman whose 2-year-old son died of
heat stroke when she left him her car last summer was sentenced
Friday to a maximum seven years in prison for manslaughter.
   Mark Mahon, attorney for Delores Lynn Blok, had asked Circuit
Judge David C. Wiggins to order probation and allow Mrs. Blok to
