<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Gambling,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Casino Rejected In Recount</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO VISTA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ballot proposal to create Northern
California's largest gambling hall in the small river town of Rio
Vista was defeated Friday in a recount of last week's close vote.
   The measure, which appeared to have won approval by a two-vote
margin, was defeated after a recount by Solano County election
officials showed a tie, 755 votes in favor and 755 against. A tie
means the measure is rejected.
   The proposal would have established an extensive cardroom that
supporters said would bring millions of dollars annually into the
strapped coffers of the community southwest of Sacramento.
   The action marks the second time the controversial proposal has
gone before local voters. Last November, the measure was defeated
by 30 votes.
   Opponents were led by local church officials, while proponents
included business interests who said the measure would stimulate
the area's economy.
