<HEAD>Warships From Five Countries Prepare for NATO Exercises</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Warships from the United States and four
other NATO members were activated Friday to participate in
monthlong exercises in the Mediterranean.
   NATO flags went up on the frigates Thomas C. Hart of the United
States, Achilles of Britain, Bremen of West Germany and Perseo of
Italy and the Turkish destroyer Kilikalipasa.
   The ships form the ``Allied On-Call Force Mediterranean,'' a
unit activated twice a year for North Atlantic Treaty Organization
maneuvers.
   A NATO statement issued in Naples said the ``Deterrent Force
1-88'' exercises will include training in warfare, communications,
seamanship and replenishment.
   Also taking part will be other surface ships, submarines, patrol
boats, aircraft and helicopters, the statement said.
