<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Prices,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Audi 5000 Prices Going up 3 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Audi of America Inc. said Friday that the
suggested retail prices of 1988 Audi 5000 Series cars will rise by
3 percent on May 9.
   The increases will range from $670 for the least expensive 5000S
sedan, making that model cost $22,850, to $1,060 for the most
expensive 5000CS Turbo Quattro wagon, which will cost $36,310, the
West German automaker's U.S. sales and distribution arm said in a
statement.
   Prices of 1988 Audi 80 and Audi 90 series cars will not be
affected, nor will option prices or transportation charges for any
models, the statement said.
</TEXT>
